I thought we configured all of our pathplanner correctly, but its going nuts. image 1257×851 44.2 KB can anybody help? i have no idea what could cause this.

for those who didnt watch the video, the robot spins very very slowly and then all of a sudden turns the motors to 100% and speeds off into a civilian. pathplanner.zip (10.9 KB)
It looks like you entered an MOI of 3,576,150. I think this value is absurd - it might be causing the problem

posts.name: Bryson Halsey
posts.cooked: I don’t believe the Robot MOI should be that high, in our code we have it set to 5.10. In PathPlanner I would reference the telemetry tab (you will need to set team number under app settings) and look at the error between commanded and actual velocities.

If you are unsure on how to calculate/select a correct value for an MOI you can use choreo’s guide:

A graphical tool for planning time-optimized trajectories for autonomous mobile robots in the FIRST Robotics Competition.
